Aston Villa 1-2 Chelsea: Paul Lambert rues 'bizarre' decisions
Media playback is not supported on this devicePaul Lambert criticises "bizarre" and "really poor" refereeing decisions aftera 2-1 home defeat by Chelseathat leaves Aston Villa involved in the relegation battle.Christian Benteke gave Aston Villa the lead against the visitors, who had Ramires sent off, before the Belgian striker also received a red card. Two goals from Frank Lampard then secured victory for Chelsea.The defeat means Villa could still go down if Wigan beat Arsenal in midweek and then defeat Paul Lambert's men on the final day of the season.